Alex Holden <alex@linuxhacker.org> writes:
> Ever spent hours fighting with an NFS server when all you actually wanted
> to do was load a tiny embedded filesystem over the network? Look no 
> further than:
> 
ftp://ftp.linuxhacker.org/pub/kernel/initrd-tftp/initrd-tftp-0.1.patch.gz
You can make the bootrom to load your kernel with initrd from tftp server
as well. Look at netboot/etherboot packages, they are doing mainly
bootp(or dhcp) + tftp the whole kernel+ramdisk image.
